        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: use SkillSpector for agentic risk findings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis replaces ClawHub's OWASP/ASI-style agentic-risk finding generation with SkillSpector-sourced findings while keeping ClawScan/Codex as the final policy adjudicator.\n\n## Why\n\nWe want SkillSpector to be the dedicated agentic-risk evidence source. ClawScan should no longer prompt Codex to generate OWASP mappings or ClawHub-native agentic-risk finding structures. Instead, the scan worker runs SkillSpector, stores the normalized SkillSpector report, passes that evidence into Codex, and lets Codex produce only the final verdict and user guidance across SkillSpector, VirusTotal, static analysis, and artifact context.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Installs and runs SkillSpector in the Codex security scan workflow.\n- Normalizes SkillSpector JSON output and persists it on skill versions and package releases.\n- Includes SkillSpector evidence in the worker diagnostics and Codex scan prompt.\n- Removes OWASP/ASI mapping instructions from the ClawScan prompt and output schema.\n- Adds SkillSpector fields to API/schema/export/dataset normalization paths.\n- Updates the security audit UI to render SkillSpector findings directly, with coexistence fallback for older scans that only have legacy ClawScan findings.\n- Shows SkillSpector above Static analysis, renders `SkillSpector (N)` with NVIDIA attribution, displays source content snippets, and hides recommendations/Risk analysis when SkillSpector findings exist.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `bun run test src/components/SkillSecurityScanResults.test.tsx convex/securityScan.test.ts`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- Browser check on `http://127.0.0.1:3000/local-dev/local-agentic-risk-demo/security-audit`\n",
        "branch": "pe/skillspector-agentic-risk",
